    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I investigated this problem a bit, but unfortunately, didn't manage to reproduce it locally on OSX or Linux.\r\n\r\nIt seems that `tailscale` prepares the `gvisor` transport to process the request, but I can't confirm what kind of request is it. I presume that `tailscale` routine might be already closed, but `gvisor` routine hangs on [channel](https://github.com/google/gvisor/blob/master/pkg/tcpip/transport/tcp/accept.go#L315-L318).\r\n\r\nIf we consider [another issue](https://github.com/google/gvisor/issues/837), I don't think that this is something we can solve.",
